1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
What if I told you a tiny atom can unlock the secrets of the past?

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:09,600
Meet Carbon-14, a radioactive isotope formed in the atmosphere.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:12,000
It decays at a known rate.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,600
This decay acts like a clock for once-living materials.

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:20,400
But it only works for items up to about 50,000 years old.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:21,200
Beyond that?

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,400
It’s a mystery.

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,800
Archaeologists and physicists rely on this method to uncover our history.

9
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,200
Want to explore more science mysteries?

10
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:30,800
Hit that follow button!
